The IP-XACT file is used to configure the pck600_lpc_q. The configuration options are:

NUM_CTRL_Q_CHL      :  Configures the number of CTRL Q-Channels. Default value is 2. Range is 2 to 3. This maps to the NUM_CTRL_Q_CHL verilog parameter.

NUM_DEV_Q_CHL       :  Configures the number of DEV Q-Channels. Default value is 1. Range is 1 to 32.

CTRL_Q_CH_SYNC      :  Includes or excludes synchronizers on CTRL Q-Channels. Default value is 1. Possible values are {0,1}. This maps to the CTRL_Q_CH_SYNC verilog parameter.

DEV_Q_CH_SYNC       :  Includes or excludes synchronizers on DEV Q-Channels. Default value is 1. Possible values are {0,1}. This maps to the DEV_Q_CH_SYNC verilog parameter.


